{
  "text": "PHLF was defined as a postoperatively acquired deterioration in the ability of the liver to maintain its synthetic, excretory, and detoxifying functions, which are characterized by an increased INR and concomitant hyperbilirubinemia (INR>1.14 and serum bilirubin more than 28 \u03bcmol/L according to the normal limits of our hospital) on or after postoperative day 5 according to the ISGLS definition [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
